{"description":"Throwing a checked exception inside when overriding a method that throws a checked exception should be allowed, as it is explicitly defined by the signature.\r\n\r\n{code}\r\ninterface I {\r\n   void foo() throws CheckedException;\r\n}\r\n\r\nabstract class A {\r\n  public abstract void bar() throws CheckedException;\r\n}\r\n\r\nclass B extends A implements I {\r\n  @Override\r\n  public void foo() throws CheckedException {\r\n    throw new CheckedException(); // should be compliant\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  @Override\r\n  public void bar() throws CheckedException {\r\n    throw new CheckedException(); // should be compliant\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n{code}","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"3.10"}